<subSubSection id="C3646548337AFF8DC79893B1FE6C22F3" pageId="3" pageNumber="132" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC136C3337AFF8DC79893B1FE6C22F3" blockId="3.[151,1436,151,1215]" pageId="3" pageNumber="132">
<emphasis id="B90AEAD1337AFF8DC79893B1FE8024B0" bold="true" box="[199,329,741,764]" pageId="3" pageNumber="132">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C7E4D40337AFF8DC60F93B1FE3E24B0" box="[336,503,740,764]" class="Insecta" family="Sisyridae" genus="Sisyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="132" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elongata">
<emphasis id="B90AEAD1337AFF8DC60F93B1FE3E24B0" box="[336,503,740,764]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="132">Sisyra elongata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEF4B32337AFF8DC59D93B1FC7424B0" author="Penny" box="[706,957,741,764]" pageId="3" pageNumber="132" refString="Penny, N. D. &amp; Rafael, J. A. (1982) Two new species of Sisyridae (Neuroptera) from the Amazon Basin. Neuroptera International, 2, 53 - 58." type="journal article" year="1982">Penny &amp; Rafael (1982)</bibRefCitation>
from Manaus, 
<collectingCountry id="F3697653337AFF8DC33C93B1FB6124B0" box="[1123,1192,741,764]" name="Brazil" pageId="3" pageNumber="132">Brazil</collectingCountry>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEF4B32337AFF8DC3EB93B1FAFD24B0" author="Flint" box="[1204,1332,741,764]" pageId="3" pageNumber="132" refString="Flint, O. S. Jr. (2006) New species and records of Neotropical Sisyridae with special reference to Sisyra (Insecta: Neuroptera). Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 119, 279 - 286." type="journal article" year="2006">Flint (2006)</bibRefCitation>
provided additional diagnostic characters, a redescription and a new record from 
<collectingRegion id="49BAF821337AFF8DC499925CFBD92553" box="[966,1040,776,799]" country="Peru" name="Loreto" pageId="3" pageNumber="132">Loreto</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3697653337AFF8DC340925CFB9A2553" box="[1055,1107,776,799]" name="Peru" pageId="3" pageNumber="132">Peru</collectingCountry>
; thereafter, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEF4B32337AFF8DC384925CFA552553" author="Monserrat" box="[1243,1436,776,799]" pageId="3" pageNumber="132" refString="Monserrat, V. J. (2005) Nuevos datos sobre algunas pequenas familias de neuropteros (Insecta: Neuroptera: Nevrorthidae, Osmylidae, Sisyridae, Dilaridae). Heteropterus: Revista de Entomologia, 5, 1 - 26." type="journal article" year="2005">Monserrat (2005)</bibRefCitation>
provided diagnostic characters and illustrations of the female genitalia of this species, and expanded its distribution to the east of 
<collectingCountry id="F3697653337AFF8DC7BA9219FEE02528" box="[229,297,845,868]" name="Brazil" pageId="3" pageNumber="132">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, in the state of 
<collectingRegion id="49BAF821337AFF8DC6919219FDC52528" box="[462,524,845,868]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="3" pageNumber="132">Bahía</collectingRegion>
(
<figureCitation id="13452A46337AFF8DC5449219FD912528" box="[539,600,845,868]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,244,1978,2000]" captionTargetBox="[186,1394,233,1922]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,194,1955]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Sisyra elongata (Neuroptera: Sisyridae). a) male habitus, dorsal view (abdomen partially omitted); b) known (black circles, based on literature) and new geographical records (red star)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/892627/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="132">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
b), a report remarkably distant from the previous records from the Amazonia. The temporal distribution of the known records of this species includes January (
<collectingCountry id="F3697653337AFF8DC3579224FBF725CB" box="[1032,1086,880,903]" name="Peru" pageId="3" pageNumber="132">Peru</collectingCountry>
), March (
<collectingRegion id="49BAF821337AFF8DC3F89224FB2025CB" box="[1191,1257,880,903]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="3" pageNumber="132">Bahía</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3697653337AFF8DC3AA9224FAF325CB" box="[1269,1338,880,903]" name="Brazil" pageId="3" pageNumber="132">Brazil</collectingCountry>
), August (Brazilian Amazonia) and September (Brazilian Amazonia and 
<collectingCountry id="F3697653337AFF8DC46292C6FC6225E5" box="[829,939,914,937]" name="Colombia" pageId="3" pageNumber="132">Colombia</collectingCountry>
). There is few information on dietary habits of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E4D40337AFF8DC7C892E1FF332580" box="[151,250,949,972]" class="Insecta" family="Sisyridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="132" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Sisyridae</taxonomicName>
adults, however fungi hyphae and spores, fragments of mites and scales, setae and other fragments of unidentified arthropods, as well as pollen and siliceous material have been reported from the gut content of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E4D40337AFF8DC27C9283FE95225D" authority="Monserrat 2005" authorityName="Monserrat" authorityYear="2005" class="Insecta" family="Sisyridae" genus="Sisyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="132" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elongata">
<emphasis id="B90AEAD1337AFF8DC27C9283FA5525A3" box="[1315,1436,983,1007]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="132">S. elongata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFEF4B32337AFF8DC7C192AEFE9D225D" author="Monserrat" box="[158,340,1018,1041]" pageId="3" pageNumber="132" refString="Monserrat, V. J. (2005) Nuevos datos sobre algunas pequenas familias de neuropteros (Insecta: Neuroptera: Nevrorthidae, Osmylidae, Sisyridae, Dilaridae). Heteropterus: Revista de Entomologia, 5, 1 - 26." type="journal article" year="2005">Monserrat 2005</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. There are two other species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E4D40337AFF8DC5E192AEFC33225D" authority="Banks, 1908" authorityName="Banks" authorityYear="1908" box="[702,1018,1017,1041]" class="Insecta" family="Sisyridae" genus="Sisyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="132" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apicalis">
<emphasis id="B90AEAD1337AFF8DC5E192AEFCAB225D" box="[702,866,1017,1041]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="132">Sisyra apicalis</emphasis>
Banks, 1908
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E4D40337AFF8DC36492AEFA5E225D" authority="Penny, 1981" authorityName="Penny" authorityYear="1981" box="[1083,1431,1018,1041]" class="Insecta" family="Sisyridae" genus="Sisyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="132" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amazonica">
<emphasis id="B90AEAD1337AFF8DC36492AEFB37225D" box="[1083,1278,1018,1041]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="132">Sisyra amazonica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFEF4B32337AFF8DC25492AEFA5E225D" author="Penny" box="[1291,1431,1018,1041]" pageId="3" pageNumber="132" refString="Penny, N. D. (1981) Neuroptera of the Amazon Basin. Part 1. Sisyridae. Acta Amazonica, 11, 157 - 169. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / 1809 - 43921981111157" type="journal article" year="1981">Penny, 1981</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, morphologically very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E4D40337AFF8DC6A59549FDBD2278" box="[506,628,1052,1076]" class="Insecta" family="Sisyridae" genus="Sisyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="132" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elongata">
<emphasis id="B90AEAD1337AFF8DC6A59549FDBD2278" box="[506,628,1052,1076]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="132">S. elongata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The three species have gonocoxites 9 elongated, however in 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E4D40337AFF8DC27E9549FA522278" box="[1313,1435,1052,1076]" class="Insecta" family="Sisyridae" genus="Sisyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="132" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elongata">
<emphasis id="B90AEAD1337AFF8DC27E9549FA522278" box="[1313,1435,1052,1076]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="132">S. elongata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
they are expanded at the distal third, with dense apicomedial brush of setae (
<bibRefCitation id="EFEF4B32337AFF8DC49F9514FBFD221B" author="Flint" box="[960,1076,1088,1111]" pageId="3" pageNumber="132" refString="Flint, O. S. Jr. (2006) New species and records of Neotropical Sisyridae with special reference to Sisyra (Insecta: Neuroptera). Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 119, 279 - 286." type="journal article" year="2006">Flint 2006</bibRefCitation>
). Gonocoxites 9 are parallel sided in 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E4D40337AFF8DC7E79536FEE52235" box="[184,300,1121,1145]" class="Insecta" family="Sisyridae" genus="Sisyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="132" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apicalis">
<emphasis id="B90AEAD1337AFF8DC7E79536FEE52235" box="[184,300,1121,1145]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="132">S. apicalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with basomedial projections on the lower and upper surfaces (
<bibRefCitation id="EFEF4B32337AFF8DC35C9536FB442235" author="Penny" box="[1027,1165,1122,1145]" pageId="3" pageNumber="132" refString="Penny, N. D. (1981) Neuroptera of the Amazon Basin. Part 1. Sisyridae. Acta Amazonica, 11, 157 - 169. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / 1809 - 43921981111157" type="journal article" year="1981">Penny 1981</bibRefCitation>
). On the other hand, 
<taxonomicName id="4C7E4D40337AFF8DC2D79536FEC322D0" class="Insecta" family="Sisyridae" genus="Sisyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="132" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amazonica">
<emphasis id="B90AEAD1337AFF8DC2D79536FEC322D0" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="132">S. amazonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has gonocoxites 9 gradually tapering and without dorsal or ventral basal projections (
<bibRefCitation id="EFEF4B32337AFF8DC3F395D1FAF922D0" author="Penny" box="[1196,1328,1157,1180]" pageId="3" pageNumber="132" refString="Penny, N. D. (1981) Neuroptera of the Amazon Basin. Part 1. Sisyridae. Acta Amazonica, 11, 157 - 169. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / 1809 - 43921981111157" type="journal article" year="1981">Penny 1981</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEF4B32337AFF8DC26395D1FED522F3" author="Penny" pageId="3" pageNumber="132" refString="Penny, N. D. &amp; Rafael, J. A. (1982) Two new species of Sisyridae (Neuroptera) from the Amazon Basin. Neuroptera International, 2, 53 - 58." type="journal article" year="1982">Penny &amp; Rafael 1982</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFEF4B32337AFF8DC67995FCFE5022F3" author="Flint" box="[294,409,1192,1215]" pageId="3" pageNumber="132" refString="Flint, O. S. Jr. (2006) New species and records of Neotropical Sisyridae with special reference to Sisyra (Insecta: Neuroptera). Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 119, 279 - 286." type="journal article" year="2006">Flint 2006</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
